<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>Hello, when I press the <code>C-c .</code> in an Org file the calendar shows up then I can pick a day. The date is entered in this form: <code>&lt;2022-08-06 Sat&gt;</code>. I recently installed Prot&#39;s &quot;denote&quot; package and I noticed that his package inserts dates in this format: <code>[2022-08-06 Sat 21:56]</code> which I personally like more. Is it possible to make <code>C-c .</code> insert the date in the <code>[2022-08-06 Sat 21:56]</code> format too?</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/zoliky"> /u/zoliky </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/whvn3p/inserting_date_in_org_document_with_cc/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/whvn3p/inserting_date_in_org_document_with_cc/">[comments]</a></span>